abstract="Information technologies are seen as a new ecology of individuals, culture, and sociality. Particular attention is paid to changes in the lifecycle of information, tectonics (info-tectonics), and digital discourse of the electronic culture, to transformation of the mechanisms of data processing and transmission, and infogenesis of the media--social space. As constituents of the information--communication--technology (ICT) complex, the largest technological matrices (electronic culture, nano-, bio-, info-, and cogno-technologies (NBIC technologies)) and certain fields (the Internet of Things, Big Data, and artificial intelligence) are analyzed.",
